BungieNet.Engine.Contract.Destiny.World..subtitle: Legendary Titan
BungieNet.Engine.Contract.Destiny.World..name: Saint-14
BungieNet.Engine.Contract.Destiny.World..description: A legendary hero and the former Titan Vanguard, Saint-14 disappeared into the Infinite Forest only to be later rescued by a fellow Guardian.

interactions.flavorLineOne:
You've returned Saint-14's old Fusion Rifle, Bastion, to him. He fiddles with the rifle briefly and sets the damaged connections straight with the component you had. The rifle hums to life.

He thanks you for finding the source of his Light and laments that his weaponry was used against Guardians. "Never again," he whispers, before handing the gun back.

You approach Saint-14; the crest of his helm brims with sunlight. "You are ready. I can feel it!" He straightens his stance and looks you over.

"Guardian, the Trials of Osiris are not simply here to train you." His voice grows out of a low rolling timbre of consideration. "I am here to assess your propensity for leadership," Saint mimics a delivery reminiscent of Osiris as he speaks.

Serious now: "The Darkness is coming. The Moon is only the first glimpse. I know it." He looks into your eyes. "When it arrives, we will need heroes, leaders, as we did at the Gap, at Six Fronts." He leans in. "The others… they will look to you." Saint nods. "You will make me proud."
Saint-14 opens his arms to you when you arrive with his gift. He accepts the cookies, sets them aside, and then clasps your hand warmly. He wishes you a happy Dawning.

Saint-14 bows his head to you. "A fellow warrior of the Light. Come close, let me guide your path to the Lighthouse, my friend." Saint explains that to enter the Trials of Osiris, you must posess a Trials Ticket. Your ticket will track your wins and losses. Each ticket has a different powerful effect.

 Saint looks over a blank ticket. "You want as many wins as possible, obviously…" he chuckles, "but do not lose three matches, or you are done." He continues that seven wins with no losses grants access to the Lighthouse for Flawless Rewards. "I await your ascension to the Lighthouse. Good luck."

You can reset your Trials Passage on the item in your Pursuits, or on the Trials of Osiris activity node.

Saint-14 is overjoyed that you have chosen to take part in the Trials of Osiris. He tries to contain his excitement as he delivers his wonderfully rehearsed speech. Afterward, he nods and says, "I know you will give this everything, Guardian. You've never been one to hold back."

Saint-14 reaches out and shakes your hand. "It is good to see you, Guardian. I have a small problem." Saint produces a display, signal-locked to a source of Light in the Tangled Shore. The signal is weak, but aligns perfectly with the frequency of Saint-14's Light from the Sundial and your newfound chronometric core. "It cannot be me. I am here." Saint laughs nervously.

"Zavala tells me you have… friends in the Tangled Shore." Saint crosses his arms. "I do not think the Fallen would react so well to my presence." He chuckles, unfolds an arm to reveal a data pad, and requests you go in his stead.

Saint-14 takes the weapon frame from you, holding it as if it is something very precious. "This," he says, looking up from the frame, "was used during the Battle of Twilight Gap. That battle was one of the moments that helped define what we, as a City, stand for."

He hands the frame back to you. "The people of the Last City came together as one to fight that battle, Guardians and Lightless alike. If you could repair this, we would recover an important piece of our history. A symbol of what it means to be a Guardian." He considers the frame in your hands, thinking. "Perhaps, in the ruins of Twilight Gap, you could recover the materials to return this weapon to its former glory."

Your zeal is noted, friend, but your Light requires refinement. As the acting Officiator of the Trials of Osiris, Saint-14 has assessed the necessary requirements for entry. His assessment has set the entry bar at a measurable Power of 960. While every Guardian has strength in their own right, some do not yet have the battle experience to operate seemlessly in a Trials fireteam.

Reach Power 960 to participate in the Trials of Osiris.
Earn Trials engrams by competing in the Trials of Osiris and returning the tokens you earn.
Show Saint-14 proof of your deeds in the Trials of Osiris.
Earn Trials engrams by competing in the Trials of Osiris and returning the tokens you earn.
